04:23.090 --> 04:28.390
All you need to do is perform a Google search for Gravatar.

04:28.400 --> 04:30.730
Here is the official Gravatar Web site.

04:30.740 --> 04:32.810
It's Gravatar dot com.

04:32.810 --> 04:36.800
And from this Web site you can create a free Gravatar account.

04:36.860 --> 04:42.290
So just like you would create a free account with services like Twitter or Facebook or Pinterest you

04:42.290 --> 04:48.290
create an account with the Gravatar service now creating and setting up your Gravatar account is very

04:48.290 --> 04:50.030
simple very intuitive.

04:50.060 --> 04:52.140
So we don't need to walk through it together.

04:52.220 --> 04:54.860
But I do want to stress one key point.

04:55.100 --> 05:01.610
When you sign up for your Gravatar account be sure that you use the same e-mail address that you used

05:01.700 --> 05:04.620
for your Wordpress administrator account.

05:04.640 --> 05:10.820
What I mean by that is if I jump back to my wordpress admin dashboard and in the sidebar if I click

05:10.820 --> 05:12.130
on users.

05:12.560 --> 05:16.450
So at the moment you probably just have the one admin account of yours.

05:16.640 --> 05:22.880
So whatever e-mail address you used for that account be sure you use that same e-mail address when you

05:22.880 --> 05:28.180
create your Gravatar account as long as that e-mail address lines up and matches.

05:28.220 --> 05:30.410
You don't need to do anything else.

05:30.410 --> 05:36.230
WordPress will automatically look for your e-mail address within the Gravatar service and it will begin

05:36.230 --> 05:38.720
pulling in your profile photo.

05:38.720 --> 05:43.310
All right so now you know how to associate an avatar with your user account.

05:43.310 --> 05:48.350
Feel free to pause this lesson and go create a Gravatar account right now if you'd like to.

05:48.530 --> 05:55.040
And now let's change gears and learn how to create new user accounts within WordPress.

05:55.100 --> 05:55.430
Right.

05:55.430 --> 06:01.800
Because maybe we want to invite a friend or a family member or a coworker to help us manage the Web

06:01.800 --> 06:02.310
site.

06:02.450 --> 06:06.100
Maybe we want multiple authors on the Web site.

06:06.170 --> 06:07.600
It's super easy to set up.

06:07.640 --> 06:08.670
So check this out.

06:08.840 --> 06:16.460
Let's jump back to our admin dashboard and in the sidebar when we hover over the users option within

06:16.460 --> 06:21.040
this pop out menu we see an item named add new.

06:21.320 --> 06:26.810
So go ahead and click on Add new and then from this screen we just need to fill in a bit of info about

06:26.810 --> 06:30.950
our colleague or friend or family member that we want to invite.

06:30.950 --> 06:33.450
So first let's give them a user name.

06:33.500 --> 06:39.710
In my case since I'm acting like my cat is the main administrator of the web site I will pretend that

06:39.710 --> 06:42.470
my cat is inviting me to contribute.

06:42.470 --> 06:50.690
So for the new username account I will say Brad then enter the new person's email address and you can

06:50.690 --> 06:53.530
fill out these fields but they are not required.

06:53.720 --> 06:59.630
Now when it comes to the password for this new account WordPress will generate a really long secure

06:59.630 --> 07:02.150
password for us automatically.

07:02.300 --> 07:05.290
If you want to see the passwords you can keep note of it.

07:05.300 --> 07:07.810
Just go ahead and click the show password button.

07:07.850 --> 07:13.340
Otherwise you can just make sure that this box is checked and then WordPress will send the new user

07:13.340 --> 07:20.300
an email with an activation link they can click where they can immediately choose their own new password.

07:20.300 --> 07:25.910
Now before we click this add new user button I want to bring your attention to this role field because

07:25.910 --> 07:29.350
this is perhaps the most important thing on this screen.

07:29.420 --> 07:33.830
So when I click on this field I can choose between five different options.

07:33.860 --> 07:39.520
Subscriber contributor author editor and administrator.

07:39.530 --> 07:44.680
Now in just a moment I will explain what each of these five options means in detail.

07:44.750 --> 07:49.910
But before we jump into that I just want to say that this field is basically just asking you the question

07:50.240 --> 07:55.150
How much do you trust this new person that you're inviting into your wordpress.

07:55.280 --> 08:00.100
OK and then based on how much you trust that person or how much faith you want to place in that person

08:00.410 --> 08:03.060
you choose a role level accordingly.

08:03.200 --> 08:06.460
So now let's go through these options one by one.

08:06.620 --> 08:11.690
I'm actually going to go through them in the opposite order that WordPress lists them because I think

08:11.690 --> 08:13.300
this makes more sense.

08:13.310 --> 08:14.970
So let's start with administrator.

08:14.990 --> 08:15.980
What does that mean.

08:16.100 --> 08:22.740
Well that's basically full access and control of literally everything within your Wordpress Web site.

08:22.970 --> 08:28.250
That's the role that your current user admin account has right throughout this course.

08:28.250 --> 08:29.970
You have been the administrator.

08:30.120 --> 08:36.690
So you have full rights and privileges to change anything unless you really truly trust someone and

08:36.690 --> 08:38.380
they have great technical skills.

08:38.520 --> 08:42.410
I probably wouldn't grant them full administrator access.

08:42.540 --> 08:45.030
OK let's move on to the editor role.

08:45.150 --> 08:51.690
So an editor has permissions to create and edit any post so they can create their own posts.

08:51.720 --> 08:58.260
They can edit and change other people's posts and they can fully publish the content up live on to the

08:58.260 --> 08:59.120
Web site.

08:59.340 --> 09:02.130
Next let's talk about the author role.

09:02.190 --> 09:08.790
So an author can create and edit their own posts but they cannot edit any other posts that were created

09:08.790 --> 09:10.080
by other people.

09:10.110 --> 09:12.490
So an author has a little bit of independence.

09:12.540 --> 09:17.700
They can create a draft for a post and then indeed they can also publish that post live up onto the

09:17.700 --> 09:23.460
Web site but they're kind of locked into their own sandbox because they can't make changes to any other

09:23.460 --> 09:24.900
author's posts.

09:24.900 --> 09:32.130
Next let's talk about the contributor role a contributor can create a draft for a post but they can't

09:32.190 --> 09:37.480
actually publish it live up onto the Web site for the whole world to view.

09:37.620 --> 09:43.930
So the contributor role is a great option if you want someone to help write guest posts for your website.

09:43.950 --> 09:49.860
They can sign in and create rough drafts for post but then it's up to an editor or an administrator

09:50.040 --> 09:53.850
to review their post and finalize it or publish it.

09:53.890 --> 10:00.990
Also once an editor or an administrator does indeed publish a contributor's post from that point forward

10:00.990 --> 10:03.430
the contributor cannot make changes to it.

10:03.540 --> 10:08.820
So the contributor just creates the rough draft and then once it gets published it's out of their hands.

10:08.820 --> 10:14.280
At that point it's up to the administrators and the editors to make any future changes to the article

10:14.340 --> 10:15.660
if necessary.

10:15.660 --> 10:20.910
And finally let's talk about the subscriber role a subscriber can't really do anything.

10:21.000 --> 10:24.260
They can't even create rough drafts for blog posts.

10:24.390 --> 10:30.470
All the subscriber can do is sign in and change their first name last name and nickname that's it.

10:30.480 --> 10:33.820
You might be wondering why the subscriber role even exists.

10:33.960 --> 10:36.420
Well it's outside the scope of this course.

10:36.540 --> 10:42.240
But when you get into more advanced things like e-commerce where if you try to create the next big social

10:42.240 --> 10:48.400
network like Facebook there are plug ins that can help you create those sorts of things within Wordpress

10:48.630 --> 10:55.140
and in those types of cases advanced plugin developers can do some pretty creative things with the subscriber

10:55.160 --> 11:00.990
role but within the context of this course and what we are trying to achieve with user accounts we don't

11:00.990 --> 11:03.630
have any real need for the subscriber role.

11:03.720 --> 11:08.130
Now that weve gone over these five roles Let's get back to the task at hand.

